article.headline: Ohio 83, Marshall 62
article.story: HUNTINGTON, W.Va. (AP) --Mychal Green scored 17 points to lead Ohio to an 83-62 win over Marshall on Saturday. Ohio also got 14 points and 12 rebounds from Leon Williams, with 12 points and nine rebounds coming in the second half. Sonny Troutman and Jeremy Fears added 11 apiece for the Bobcats (16-9, 10-6 Mid-American Conference). The victory was Ohio's eighth in 10 games, while Marshall dropped its fourth straight contest. The loss gives Marshall (5-20, 2-14) its first 20-loss season since 1991-1992 when the team finished 7-22. Marshall received 13 points and eight rebounds from Mark Patton on the inside, while David Anderson chipped in with 10 points. The Bobcats shot better than 60 percent in each half and finished 35-of-55 from the floor (63.6 percent).<
